<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);">These instructions take advantage =
of the&nbsp;</span><a href=3D"https://getcomposer.org/" style=3D"font-size:=
 14.0px;line-height: 1.4285715;" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">C=
omposer</a><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);"> powered update systems in=
 5.4 for maintenance updates, so&nbsp;</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,5=
1,51);font-size: 14.0px;line-height: 1.4285715;">make sure:</span></p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);font-size: 14.0px;line-height: 1.42=
85715;">Familiarize yourself with the </span><span class=3D"confluence-link=
">&nbsp;</span><a href=3D"/display/EZP/Using+Composer"><span class=3D"confl=
uence-link">Using Composer</span></a><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);fo=
nt-size: 14.0px;line-height: 1.4285715;"> page.</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);">Update Composer, as found on&nbsp=
;<a href=3D"https://getcomposer.org/doc/03-cli.md#self-update" class=3D"ext=
ernal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Composer self-update documentation</a></span><=
/li>
</ul>
<p><em><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);">For Upgrading from versions pr=
ior to 5.3 look at the&nbsp;<a href=3D"/display/EZP/Installation+and+Upgrad=
e+Guides">Installation and Upgrade Guides</a>.</span></em></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);">You will also find, at the end of =
this document, a list of <a href=3D"#id-5.4.xUpdateInstructions-new-package=
s">new, optional packages</a> that were made available during the maintenan=
ce phase of this version.</span></p>
<h1 id=3D"id-5.4.xUpdateInstructions-BeforeUpdating">Before&nbsp;Updating</=
h1>
<p>Follow <u>all*</u> instructions below that applies to the version you're=
&nbsp;updating&nbsp;from: when updating from 5.4.0 everything applies.</p>
<p><em>* The version you update to will always be the latests, hence the im=
portance of following all steps.</em></p>
<h2 id=3D"id-5.4.xUpdateInstructions-From5.4.6andlower">From 5.4.6 and lowe=
r</h2>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.4.xUpdateInstructions-Updateezpublish-legacy-installertov2.0=
.3forComposer1.1">Update&nbsp;ezpublish-legacy-installer to v2.0.3 for Comp=
oser 1.1</h3>
<p>Newer versions of Composer sometimes updates it's API's and as such we n=
eed to make sure our composer plugin&nbsp;ezpublish-legacy-installer&nbsp;i=
s up-to-date before we do anything else, so if you don't already have <code=
>ezsystems/ezpublish-legacy-installer</code> v2.0.3 and Composer 1.1, do th=
e following:<span style=3D"color: rgb(0,98,147);">&nbsp;</span></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;"># First install Composer v1.0 that works with old version of ezpub=
lish-legacy-installer
php -r "copy('https://getcomposer.org/download/1.0.3/composer.phar', 'compo=
ser.phar');"

# Then install newer version
php -d memory_limit=3D-1 composer.phar update --no-dev --prefer-dist --no-s=
cripts ezsystems/ezpublish-legacy-installer

# Then make sure composer is updated to latests
php -d memory_limit=3D-1 composer.phar selfupdate&nbsp;</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"id-5.4.xUpdateInstructions-From5.4.1andlower"><span style=3D"line=
-height: 1.5;">From 5.4.1 and lower</span></h2>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.4.xUpdateInstructions-Removeunneededdependencycausingconflic=
ts">Remove unneeded dependency causing conflicts</h3>
<p>Perform the following command to make sure you you are not affected by c=
onflicts caused by this package:</p>
<div>
<div class=3D"syntaxhighlighter nogutter  bash">
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">php -d memory_limit=3D-1 composer.phar remove --no-update --dev beh=
at/mink-selenium-driver</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-tip=
">
<p class=3D"title">Recommended: Enable php-openssl extension</p>
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-approve confluence-info=
rmation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
This release fixes a vulnerability in the eZ Publish password recovery func=
tion. You need to have the PHP OpenSSL extension (ext-openssl) installed to=
 take full advantage of the improved security, but even without it security=
 is improved. See&nbsp;
<a href=3D"http://share.ez.no/community-project/security-advisories/ezsa-20=
15-001-potential-vulnerability-in-ez-publish-password-recovery" class=3D"ex=
ternal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Security Advisory</a> for further information=
.
</div>
</div>
<h2 class=3D"element" id=3D"id-5.4.xUpdateInstructions-From5.4.2andlower">F=
rom 5.4.2 and lower</h2>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.4.xUpdateInstructions-UpgradeSymfonyrequirementupdate-symfon=
y">Upgrade Symfony requirement<span class=3D"confluence-anchor-link" id=3D"=
id-5.4.xUpdateInstructions-update-symfony"></span></h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">php -d memory_limit=3D-1 composer.phar require --no-update symfony/=
symfony:~2.7.0 sensio/distribution-bundle:~3.0 </pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.4.xUpdateInstructions-FixpossibleusageoftheXmlTextCustomTags=
pre-converters">Fix possible usage of the XmlText CustomTags pre-converters=
</h3>
<p>The XmlText fix for EZP-23513 (see&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://github.com/ez=
systems/ezpublish-kernel/pull/1087" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow=
">https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/pull/1087</a>) deprecates/r=
emoves the CustomTags pre-converter in favor of a new Expanding converter. =
While they're not part of the public API, if you rely on this file in any w=
ay, you might want to check and update your code.</p>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.4.xUpdateInstructions-Updatetherewriterulesconfiguration"><s=
trong>Update the rewrite rules configuration</strong></h3>
<p>The legacy, v1 REST API, is now integrated to the Symfony Kernel. This a=
llows interaction between this channel and new stack caches (persistence an=
d HTTP). It mainly affects the Content Staging legacy extension. Remove the=
 following line from your rewrite rules and restart your web server:</p>
<h4 id=3D"id-5.4.xUpdateInstructions-apache">apache</h4>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">RewriteRule ^/api/[^/]+/v1/ /index_rest.php [L]</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h4 id=3D"id-5.4.xUpdateInstructions-nginx">nginx</h4>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">rewrite "^/api/[^/]+/v1" "/index_rest.php" last;</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"id-5.4.xUpdateInstructions-From5.4.4orlower">From 5.4.4 or lower<=
/h2>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.4.xUpdateInstructions-EnabletheLegacySearchEngineBundleinthe=
kernel">Enable the LegacySearchEngineBundle in the kernel</h3>
<p>Edit&nbsp;<code>ezpublish/EzPublishKernel.php</code>, and instantiate&nb=
sp;<code>eZ\Bundle</code><code>\</code><code>EzPublishLegacySearchEngineBun=
dle</code><code>\</code><code>EzPublishLegacySearchEngineBundle</code>&nbsp=
;in the list of enabled bundles in the&nbsp;<code>$bundles</code>&nbsp;arra=
y in the&nbsp;<code>registerBundles()</code>&nbsp;method,&nbsp;right before=
&nbsp;<code>EzPublishLegacyBundle</code>.</p>
<h2 id=3D"id-5.4.xUpdateInstructions-From5.4.5orlower">From 5.4.5 or lower<=
/h2>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.4.xUpdateInstructions-Checksymfonyrequirement">Check symfony=
 requirement</h3>
<p>Make sure you are using Symfony 2.7, as Symfony 2.8 is currently not sup=
ported <em>(both are LTS releases, but 2.8 introduced a few breaks that cau=
ses problems)</em>. So check version using command below, and if 2.8 <a hre=
f=3D"#id-5.4.xUpdateInstructions-update-symfony">follow instuctions above</=
a> to correct it:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">php -d memory_limit=3D-1 composer.phar show --installed</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"id-5.4.xUpdateInstructions-Updatingpackageswithcomposer">Updating=
 packages with composer</h2>
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p>With this command you'll update all packages that have received updates:=
</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;"># First delete the Symfony container cache to avoid error, on Wind=
ows use something like: DEL /F /Q /S ezpublish/cache/*/*ProjectContainer.ph=
p
rm ezpublish/cache/*/*ProjectContainer.php
&nbsp;
php -d memory_limit=3D-1 composer.phar update --no-dev --prefer-dist
</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-tip=
">
<p class=3D"title">Tip: Legacy extension autoload</p>
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-approve confluence-info=
rmation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>Legacy extensions autoload must be regenerated when new classes are adde=
d. To make sure to avoid any issues always run this command after composer =
update:</p>
<p><code>php ezpublish/console ezpublish:legacy:script bin/php/ezpgeneratea=
utoloads.php --extension</code></p>
</div>
</div>
<h1 id=3D"id-5.4.xUpdateInstructions-AfterUpdating"><span>After Updating</s=
pan></h1>
<p><span>Follow all instructions below that applies to the version&nbsp;you=
've updated from, i.e. if you are updating from 5.4.0 everything applies.</=
span></p>
<h2 id=3D"id-5.4.xUpdateInstructions-Updatingfrom5.4.1andlower">Updating fr=
om 5.4.1 and lower</h2>
<h3 class=3D"wordwrap" id=3D"id-5.4.xUpdateInstructions-UpdateSolrconfigura=
tionandreindexcontent">Update Solr configuration and reindex content</h3>
<p>An eZ Find user needs to update their solr <code>schema.xml</code> file.=
</p>
<p>For each solr core (located in <code>ezfind/java/solr</code>), you need =
to edit&nbsp;<code>&lt;my-core-name&gt;/conf/schema.xml</code></p>
<p>Around line 566, right after:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: xml; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">&lt;field name=3D"meta_priority_si" type=3D"sint" indexed=3D"true" =
stored=3D"true" multiValued=3D"true"/&gt;</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>Add the following lines:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: xml; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">&lt;!-- denormalised fields for hidden and visible path elements --=
&gt;
&lt;field name=3D"meta_visible_path_si" type=3D"sint" indexed=3D"true" stor=
ed=3D"true" multiValued=3D"true"/&gt;     &lt;!-- Visible Location path IDs=
 --&gt;
&lt;field name=3D"meta_visible_path_string_ms" type=3D"mstring" indexed=3D"=
true" stored=3D"true" multiValued=3D"true"/&gt; &lt;!-- Visible Location pa=
th string --&gt;
&lt;field name=3D"meta_hidden_path_si" type=3D"sint" indexed=3D"true" store=
d=3D"true" multiValued=3D"true"/&gt;     &lt;!-- Hidden Location path IDs -=
-&gt;
&lt;field name=3D"meta_hidden_path_string_ms" type=3D"mstring" indexed=3D"t=
rue" stored=3D"true" multiValued=3D"true"/&gt; &lt;!-- Hidden Location path=
 string --&gt;</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p><em><em>Now restart Solr, and re-index your content to be able to take a=
dvantage of this&nbsp;improvement.</em></em></p>
<h1 id=3D"id-5.4.xUpdateInstructions-Newpackages">New packages</h1>
<p>New features are sometimes backported from the development version as ex=
ternal packages. They can be installed on top of your existing installation=
.</p>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.4.xUpdateInstructions-Solrsearchengine(5.4.5)">Solr search e=
ngine (5.4.5)</h3>
